    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "16abffd1_b86f02c1",
        "filename": "tools/sk_app/MetalWindowContext.mm",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 105,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-11T14:38:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think that\u0027s what the other backends do. They wrap the client\u0027s texture in a GrTextureRenderTarget where the Skia-created render buffer has the number of samples passed to the function and it gets resolved to the client\u0027s single-sampled texture. The sample count passed to MakeFromBackendTexture is not intended to mean that the client\u0027s texture has multiple samples. We assume it always has 1.",
